Several roles of RanBP2 have emerged that implicate RanBP2 in <termsem="GO:0006913"> nucleocytoplasmic trafficking </term> [ 3,5 ] , <termsem="GO:0006412"> protein biogenesis </term> [ 6,7 ] , the <termsem="GO:0022607"> formation </term> of the <termsem="GO:0007067"> mitotic </term> spindle , <termsem="GO:0022607"> assembly </term> of the nuclear envelope [ 8 ] , and the integration of the <termsem="GO:0051081"> nuclear envelope breakdown </term> with <termsem="GO:0051382"> kinetochore formation </term> and maturation during early <termsem="GO:0007067"> mitotic </term> progression [ 9 ] .
