The LD of RanBP2 ( Figure 1A ) is a large and orphan domain of ~ 700 residues ( ~ 80 kDa ) , for which no molecular partners have been identified until this date .
Brain and retina yeast two-hybrid libraries were screened with LD .
Cox11 was identified as a partner to this domain ( Figure 1B and 1C ) .
Cox11 is a <termsem="GO:0016530"> <termsem="independent_continuant"> metallochaperone </term> </term> implicated in <termsem="GO:0008535"> <termsem="GO:0004129"> <termsem="independent_continuant"> cytochrome c oxidase </term> </term> assembly </term> [ 30,31 ] .
